For each channel, we subtract one half of the image from the other half; Firstly, we divide all channels as two equal matrix. After that we subtract them from each other. Finaly,we combine two seperated matrix for each channel. For each channel, we display each new channel.

In [87]:
def rgb2gray(rgb):
    return np.dot(rgb[...,:3], [0.299, 0.587, 0.144])
In [88]:
